{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"UnixSocketAddressRef","symbolKind":"struct","roleHeading":"Structure","externalID":"s:3GIO20UnixSocketAddressRefV","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"UnixSocketAddressRef"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"UnixSocketAddressRef"}],"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}]},"abstract":[{"text":"Support for UNIX-domain (also known as local) sockets, corresponding to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"struct sockaddr_un"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/UnixSocketAddressRef"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"UnixSocketAddressRef"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"UNIX domain sockets are generally visible in the filesystem."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"However, some systems support abstract socket names which are not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"visible in the filesystem and not affected by the filesystem"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"permissions, visibility, etc. Currently this is only supported"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"under Linux. If you attempt to use abstract sockets on other","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"systems, function calls may return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_IO_ERROR_NOT_SUPPORTED"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"errors. You can use [func"},{"code":"Gio.UnixSocketAddress.abstract_names_supported","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to see if abstract names are supported."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Since GLib 2.72, ","type":"text"},{"code":"GUnixSocketAddress","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is available on all platforms. It"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"requires underlying system support (such as Windows 10 with "},{"code":"AF_UNIX","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") at"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"run time."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before GLib 2.72, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"<gio\/gunixsocketaddress.h>"},{"text":" belonged to the UNIX-specific","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"GIO interfaces, thus you had to use the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gio-unix-2.0.pc"},{"text":" pkg-config file","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"when using it. This is no longer necessary since GLib 2.72."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/UnixSocketAddressRef"},{"text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GUnixSocketAddress"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/UnixSocketAddressProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/UnixSocketAddressRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" only as an ","type":"text"},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" reference to an existing ","type":"text"},{"code":"GUnixSocketAddress","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineCon